@ShikshaWrites It's not a bad time of year to plant tomato plants.  They have simple daily needs and grow and change so quickly, I've found them very good for propping myself up on when everything feels like a bit of a lost cause.  And you might get tomatoes!  (Smaller fruit are easier.)

@ShikshaWrites Slowing down to the absolute moment to moment helps me.  Even if every moment is painful, just working methodically through fulfilling my needs, feeling that take up time.  Journalling also, so the time passed doesn't get lost.  Remembering to push myself from time to time.
